{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}

The '''Swiss Heritage Society''' (SHS) is a [[non-profit organization|non-profit organisation]] dedicated to the advancement of [[Switzerland]]’s [[architecture|architectural]] heritage. Its focus is on the preservation of important [[landmark]]s, the development of the structural environment, and the promotion of good architectural design.

The Swiss Heritage Society was founded in 1905, has about 17,000 members and publishes the magazine ''Heimatschutz/Sauvegarde'' quarterly.

The Swiss Heritage Society pursues its goals mainly with [[public relations]] activities, through publications, technical consulting in construction projects, advisory functions in planning committees, appraisals, legal action, and financial [[Grant (money)|grants]] for pioneering projects. The SHS commends exemplary achievements by awarding prizes ([[Wakker Prize]], Heimatschutz Prize, Schulthess Horticultural Prize). Together with [[Pro Natura (Switzerland)|Pro Natura]], the SHS has been supporting the annual fundraising drive with chocolate [[Thaler|talers]] (''Schoggitaler'') for over fifty years.

